cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.AI, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the compression properties of a specific family of trees and presents an approximation algorithm for trees. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper provides a combinatorial characterization of self-nested trees. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another possibility as the paper deals with the structure of trees and their properties. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possibility as the paper discusses the practical applications of self-nested trees in answering complex queries and predicting edit distance between trees. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possibility as the paper presents an algorithm for approximating trees that can be used in fast prediction of edit distance between trees, which is a common problem in machine learning.
